	<text>
		<body>
			<p><!--Irving N. Linnell, (Telegramm), Prag, 19.10.1939, S. 1: Records of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of Czechoslovakia 1910-1944, Washington 1982 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 860F.4016/82--></p>
			<p>A general <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">removal</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">male</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> aged 17 to 70 was ordered from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070328/moravska-ostrava.html">Mahrisch-Ostrau, Bohemia</placeName> for <date
					when="1939-10-17">October 17</date> and is reported to have been carried out quite completely. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were directed to report with limited
				luggage, food for several days and money up to 3,000 crowns. Their destination has not been stated but the trains carrying them
				departed toward <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-827" type="subject">women</term> were also required to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1136" type="subject">register</term> on the same day and fear that they
				too will be sent away. Observers believe that this movement may be to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">labor camp</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/maps/google_52_20.html">Poland</placeName> for reconstruction work there. Further details are being
				sought and will be reported.</p>
		</body>
